---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Flows as human-testable documentation" description="Why Groundwork docs include complete interactive flows">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <p class="gw-caption">Wiki</p>
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Flows as human-testable documentation</h1>
        <p>Groundwork docs include full interactive journeys that show components working together in realistic application contexts.</p>

        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Why this matters</h2>
        <p>Isolated component pages prove that a component can render. They do not prove that the system works as a product surface.</p>
        <p>Flows pressure-test composition, validation, review states, keyboard navigation, and whether restrictive React APIs feel helpful in realistic use.</p>

        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">What a flow should include</h2>
        <ol class="gw-list">
          <li>A realistic user task.</li>
          <li>Happy path and error path.</li>
          <li>A visible human test script.</li>
          <li>Keyboard-only review guidance.</li>
          <li>Automated axe coverage.</li>
          <li>At least one Playwright interaction test for the core journey.</li>
          <li>Visual regression coverage for the initial state.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Current example</h2>
        <p><a class="gw-link" href="/flows/contact-details/">Contact details</a> demonstrates data entry, validation, field-level errors, review, and confirmation.</p>

        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Rule of thumb</h2>
        <p>If a component looks fine in isolation but feels awkward inside a flow, the flow is probably telling the truth. Fix the API or pattern before adding more examples.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
